==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: deflate
<hw>de*flate"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>de-</ets> down + L. <ets>flare</ets>, <ets>flatus</ets> to
blow.]</ety> <def>To reduce from an inflated condition; used literally
and metaphorically; <as>as, to <ex>deflate</ex> a tire; to
<ex>deflate</ex> expectations</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>deflated</ent>⟦br⟧
